1.1 Introduction
-----------------

Welcome to the invitation guide to the BSE '97 or The Belgian Scene Event 1997,
the COWlest Amoooooooooooga party in Belgium in YEARS ! (The last decent Amiga
party was in 1992, the TRSi Easter conference - we all remember that one ;).


1.2 What
---------

The Belgian Scene Event 1997 will be a small but cool *AMIGA ONLY* party
held by Crux & Bad Karma in Hasselt, a town in the northwest corner of
Belgium, close to the borders of:
                 Germany         (apx. 50km.)
                 The Netherlands (apx. 30km.)
                 Luxembourgh     (apx. 40km.)
                 France          (apx. 80km.)

Don't let these distances scare you since it is a rather high aproximate ;).
Anyhow, the partyplace is at 300m of a rather big expressway, so you won't
have any troubles finding it.


1.3 Why
--------

OK, you probably wonder how we can be so mad organizing a party in a nowhere-
land like Belgium.  Well make it easy we want to prove that there IS indeed a
scene left in Belgium and that it can still organize something decent. And to
make this sure: This is not Wired 97 and it hasn't anything to do with it!

But remember that we make this party for FUN.  We dont want to make ANY money
on it, all we have left will go to the prize-money for the competitions.



                        Well, we hope we can welcome you at the BSE 1997,

                                                        CRiSP of CBK
                                                        FRaNKy of CBK


