2.1 Where and when ?
---------------------

The BSE 1997 party will take place at the last weekend of August 1997,
meaning August, the 29th, 30th and 31st. The doors will open the 29th
of August at noon (12:00) and they will close the 31th of August at
noon (12:00), so all you peeps can get home before school starts again ;).
(For a more detailed schedule, see party schedule).

The party place will be Zaal Crutzenhof in Hasselt (and that is
in the province of Limburg).

NOTE: The party-organizers are at the party place starting from Friday 29th,
      6:00 AM. If you arrive earlier, you will nothing :(

2.2 How to get there ?
-----------------------

Please don't get scared off by the lengthy texts ;) - We mentioned every
detail you can see when you drive towards the party place. It is just to
make sure that everybody gets where they have to be. Signs will be put out
everywhere, but please bring a map to be sure (the signs might get removed
by some law enforcement evil forces ;)


2.2.1 By car:
--------------

Following is a classification for every country. This has been made to make
things easier for all of us. The explanations are kept as simple as possible,
and we will place signs to lead you at every cross-section!
If you DO get lost in Hasselt, there is nothing to worry about: just follow
all directions pointing to the 'Grote Ring' (big circle-like road around the
town of Hasselt) and keep on driving around that 'Grote Ring' until you see
a sign saying either 'BSE 1997 - This way ->' or 'Kuringersteenweg'. Take the
'Kuringersteenweg' that goes INTO the town of Hasselt. If you take the
direction 'Kuringen' you will drive away. Once you're on the 'Kuringersteenweg'
just follow the instructions for Belgian people.

 Belgian people

 Just make sure you get on the E313 highway (Antwerp/Anvers/Antwerpen ->
 Köln/Cologne/Keulen). Take exit 27 (Kuringen) and just continue following the
 road you are on (this will be for a kilometer or 10)... This road is called
 the 'Kuringersteenweg'. After these 10km's you'll arrive in Hasselt, continue
 driving until you get at the Grote Ring. Here you have to cross the street
 and actually follow the road you are on. Take the third to the left
 (the Lazarijsstraat). Then (after 20 - 40m) take the first to the right.
 That is the 'Oude Kuringerbaan'. You will see the partyplace indicated by
 the 'Cristal' sign that is outside (that is a red plate with a white logo on it)


 German people:

 Okay, quite simple: Whereever you are coming from, just make sure you get on
 the E313 (also called A2 in Belgium, the A76 in The Netherlands or highway 4
 in Germany). This road runs from Aachen 'till Leuven (Louvain), but it passes
 in Genk (the town next to Hasselt). Just follow this road (immergerade aus,
 through the Netherlands, into Belgium) until you get at exit 31 (Genk). Follow
 this road until you get in the town of Diepenbeek. In Diepenbeek you just have
 to drive straight through, you will cross a rather large road that takes you
 in the center of the town of Diepenbeek, drive straight through (you have to
 pass a factory called 'Jaga') until you cross the E313 (another expressway). You
 can't miss this road, you drive up a hill - it is the only HUGE road in the damn
 place - and it is indicated with E313 - Antwerpen. Take the direction Antwerpen
 (meaning you have to turn in right). Okay, just follow this road until you get
 at exit 27 (Kuringen) and follow the instructions for the Belgian people!

 Dutch people:

 This is also quite easy, although the route may vary if you live in the
 western parts of the Netherlands. Anyhow, here we go:
 Make your way to Belgium. There are 2 major possibilities, either via
 Breda or Eindhoven.

 - Breda:
    Take the road to Antwerp, and once you're in Antwerp, follow the 'Ring'
    and take the E313, direction Liège/Luik. Keep on driving (for about 80km)
    until you get at exit 27 (Kuringen). Go off there and follow the
    instructions for Belgian users.
 - Eindhoven:
    This is a bit more complicated (meaning that you have to take some
    smaller roads). Anyhow, just make your way to Belgium, and drive to
    Hasselt (pass some cities like Hechtel-Eksel, Heusden-Zolder and Zonhoven)
    until you arrive at the 'Grote Ring' in Hasselt. Just follow that one
    (drive to the right when you get there) until you get at the 'Kuringer-
    steenweg'. Take that one (direction Hasselt, NOT Kuringen) and follow the
    instructions for Belgian users


2.2.2 By train:
---------------

By train see you get to the station of Hasselt (Limburg). The partyplace
is at 200m of the station. (For foreigners: Take the train to Brussels,
then take the first one to Hasselt/Genk & Luik/Maastricht (make sure
that you sit in the front wagons, the last ones will go to Holland :).

Here are some train-hours :

Direct trains to Hasselt leave in Brussels (station Bruxelles-Midi) at xx:18
(mostly from track 12, but check to be sure).  At xx+1:45 you'll be in
Hasselt then.

Another way is take the train to Luik & Collogne in Brussels (BXL-Midi)
at xx:48.  Get off in Leuven (the first stop after Brussels, the third after
Bruxelles-Midi) and run to platform 3 (mostly !) where you can get the train
to Hasselt/Landen at xx+1:25 (the train to Luik/Collogne will arrive in Leuven
at xx+1:17 so better be quick hehehe) to be in Hasselt at xx+2:10.

If you want to take the direct train to Hasselt in Leuven, its there at xx:47,
mostly on track 4.

On friday you will have trains till about midnight..  In the weekends aim
at 22:00 for the last train to and from Hasselt.

When you are in the front of the Hasselt station, you will see lots of
busstops in front of  you. Take the street on the RIGHT OPPOSITE hand of
the square (the F. Massystraat). You will end up at a pretty big road called
the KONINGIN ASTRIDLAAN. Walk left here and take the third one to the RIGHT.
(The Lazarijsstraat). Then (after 20m) take the first one to the LEFT
and walk straigth through (you'll cross one road). After about 100m you will see
the partyplace indicated :).

Another way to remember this is to follow all the CRISTAL signs (that's a
Belgian Beer). It is a red plate with a white sign. At the station of Hasselt,
there is this pub with a Cristal sign, go into that street (F. Massystraat),
go to the left, until you come across another cristal sign (Lazarijsstraat).
Enter it, after 20m take the first to the right until you get at another Cristal
sign, the partyplace! :)))


2.3 The cash stuff
-------------------

Entrance fee will be set at 350 BEF (Belgian francs) per person, we only
accept Belgian francs. If you really insist you can also pay in other
currencies, but keep in mind that the exchange rates are not our means
of mesure - you will pay more if you pay in other currencies!

Girls get free entrance ofcourse!

Just to give you an idea of how much 350 BEF is, here is a list with
exchange rates (we will NOT use the following list for entrance fee
money!)

 350 BEF        =       $10 or DM 18 or Fl. 20 or 60 FF
 250 BEF        =       $7 or DM 11 or Fl. 15 or 45 FF

If you want to pay in advance, no problem..  The price then is 250 BEF
(Belgian francs, same stuff as above) per person. If you pay in advance,
your money will not be refunded if you don't show up at the party, sorry.
Also no change on advance payments.

You can mail the money to:
PO BOX 25
3000 LEUVEN 3
Belgium.

With the cash send your 'password'.  We'll ask you for it at the entrance
if you claim to have payed in advance. If someone else knew about your
password and got in with your money before you..  tuff luck. Better find
the dude and kill him (OUTSIDE the party-place please !). Also add your
first name and handle please

And ofcourse if you dont like the Belgian postal service, you can use a
bank-transfer too..  The account-number is 330-0201835-32. In the message
put your handle, real name and password.


