6. Reservations
----------------

Ofcourse you are able to reserve a number of seats at the party-place. You are
strongly encouraged to reserve your seats when you are sure you are coming to
the party. We don't want to have people arriving at the partyplace when there
are no more seats left!

You can reserve your seats by writing a simple mail to the organizers
(see 7. Contact) with the following contents:
        - Your handle / first name
        - The number of seats you wish to reserve
        - The number of computers you are bringing (and preferably the model)

An example email could be:
        - Name  : Crisp
        - Seats : 5
        - Compus: 3 A1200, 2 A4000.

That's it!

If you want to pay in advance, feel free to send us the reservation sheet by
postal services. You can include the money over there or you can use a bank
account. You can also send us an email with the number of reservations and
send us the money afterwards. Please don't forget to add your password to both
the email and the money, since we won't be able to smell where it came from ;).

